obtain a SingleCellExperiment with a version of TENxPBMCData pbmc68k data

Source: R/get68proc.R
get68proc.Rd

obtain a SingleCellExperiment with a version of TENxPBMCData pbmc68k data

get68proc(cache = BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache(), targetfolder = tempdir())

Arguments

cache

a cache like that defined by BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache()

targetfolder

character(1) path, defaulting to `tempdir()`, where a serialized SingleCellExperiment will be placed

Note

An 835MB zipfile holding the output of saveHDF5SummarizedExperiment is retrieved from Open Storage Network and placed in cache. colData labels are obtained with a SingleR run using the HumanPrimaryCellAtlasData label.main.

Examples

tst = get68proc()
dir.exists(file.path(tempdir(), "p68_saved"))
